Configure port on Linux
Ignore this element.

1. 	
Start a terminal.
2. 	
As superuser, navigate to the Edge System installation directory: /opt/EdgeSystem.
3. 	
Type in the properties and their values through a command as shown in this example:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host Configuration System Port port=5590

4. 	
Stop and start the OSIsoft Edge System service by running the following commands:

systemctl stop osisoft.edgesystem.service systemctl start osisoft.edgesystem.service

5. 	
Optional: To view the configured port number, run this command:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host configuration System Port

